readme:
Service Usage

This service is used to call Qflow to create an appointment booking client within Qflow. Upon a successful processing a url text will be returned to the calling system, which allows the next step flow within the Qflow appointment booking process.

Service Behaviour

Qflow is an external system which uses JSON mesaging format. An xslt transform is required between xml and JSON message.

Service Variants

when called from ICSE, a 2 step xslt transform will be required.

The first step is from ICSE xml into Enterprise SV615 xml

The second step is from Enterprise xml into JSON.
